ALGIERS, Oct. 27 (Xinhua) -- The Algerian Football Federation (FAF) announced on Wednesday the conditional return of spectators to stadiums, according to the official APS news agency. This return, which occurs after more than 17 months of suspension due to the COVID-19 pandemic, will be subject to the conditions of compliance with the health protocol and the presentation of the health pass, the FAF said in a statement on Wednesday. The FAF specified that only those who have received two doses of the COVID-19 vaccines will be allowed to enter football stadiums. The FAF has set the reopening date of the stadiums on Oct. 30. The reopening of the stadiums to spectators came amid a sharp decline of the COVID-19 infections in Algeria. The Algerian government announced on Oct. 18 the full lifting of nationwide lockdown. Enditem